FBIS3-11614 "drlat056_a_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-056 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Mar 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Havana Notes PRC Position on U.S. Pressure FL2203182794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 22 Mar 94 FL2203182794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen stated that his country is willing to go on without trade relations with the United States if Washington continues to condition its preferential status of bilateral trade on the domestic policies issues of the PRC. In an interview published today in the NEW YORK TIMES newspaper, Qian Qichen criticized the U.S. policy of setting the deadline of July 1994 on China's most favored nation status in trade with the United States if Beijing does not make progress in the observation of human rights. It is important to remember that according to the very UN Human Rights Commission charter, the fulfilling of all its clauses are determined by the domestic and sovereign laws of each state.
